blog.description:
Claire. Whovian. Eccles Crew. Doctor x Rose. Fanfic reader, admirer, occasional writer. Doctor Who and DW-adjacent/crossover fandoms. Occasionally life, the universe & everything. Primarily RTD-era, but I love all Doctors and companions. Falling down the Big Finish rabbit hole. Everything will be seen through shipper goggles! I regularly reblog NSFW gifs, art, and fic. (Sometimes write it.) (Whatever is left post-purge may be found under lemons.) Tagger of categories, ships, content, and any random thoughts or flailing that comes to mind. 😉
A few of my favorite things: kissing, sexy lounging, prime scruff, forearms, hands, hot prof reading glasses, and smutty smutty fan art.

title: Could the Unused Tenth Doctor Story Arc of Series 5 Work for Big Finish?
body:
Could the Unused Tenth Doctor Story Arc of Series 5 Work for Big Finish?

Before David Tennant’s departure was announced, then-incoming showrunner/head writer Steven Moffat had some very different ideas for Series 5, which could have involved the Tenth Doctor travelling with Amy Pond, instead of Matt Smith.
